column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: System Damage -  When a System fully breaks due to fire or boarders, the hull also takes one damage.

You locate the highest concentration of life forms and bring the ship alongside the station. Before you can begin to offload the survivors, a huge blast splits the station apart. Your ship is thrown away and some debris pierces your hull. You watch helplessly as the last of the survivors are consumed in the collapse of the station.
You access the recent scans from the unguarded station. Your map has been updated with details of the surrounding area.
Your jump leads you to nothing but empty space. This Jump Beacon serves no purpose other than as a connection.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Great. Take this bit of fuel as a down-payment. We'll be one step behind you, following your jump signatures. Don't want to take any risks now, do we? Added a quest marker to your map!
Federation sympathizers contact you as you arrive. We know your mission should be secret, so don't ask how we know about it. Take this schematic, it's all we can do to help.
Shortly after you arrive, the ship you were escorting jumps nearby. They thank you for your help and offer you a reward.
The space station here has a traveling merchant who shows you his wares.
column12: Crew: Rock, Engi, Human, Weapon: LASER HULL 1, BEAM LONG, SHOTGUN, System: teleporter, mind, hacking,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a collection of useful scrap material.
The pirate's victim quickly jumps away before you have a chance to speak to them.
Thank you for your business, no refunds!
You're far from Federation home space here in Zoltan territory, and it's not clear whether the authorities will have any goodwill remaining. Still, you have to push forward.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

When he sees you have emerged victorious, the Zoltan wise man enters a rage. Rifts threaten to tear space apart until, instead, the Zoltan implodes, sending a blast wave of scrap and salvage dragged here from distant worlds in your direction.

We have been studying the relationships between the species and have determined that the 'Federation' still has potential to be a net positive for the galaxy. Please accept this gift to aid your journey.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The Zoltan are fascinated by other species, and have set up something of an alien knick-knack shop here. Why not take a look?

column11: You stumble upon some Zoltan military vessels engaging in combat training. Their Energy Shields are impressive, but you note how quickly beam and ion weaponry take them down.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Your crew are constantly looking out of the windows, checking for hostiles. They jump at every creak and moan of the ship. The tension is almost palpable...
A brief exploration yields nothing of interest.
You have arrived in Engi space. The Mantis have been threatening the Engi core worlds, but you should be able to stock up for your journey.
You transfer down some missile warheads and the Engi rig them to blow before setting a distress signal to attract the fleet's attention.
If you take the fuel at least it won't come into the hands of of the Rebels. You breach the containment and access what remains of the fuel reserves.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Engi can't feel fear, so they bear you no ill will when you explain you're unwilling to help. They set off on their journey and you do the same.
There are no more life-signs remaining on the ship. You strip it of useful materials.
An Engi ship hails: Engine upgrade necessary for travel home. Sale of equipment necessary for engine upgrade.

The civilian ship wisely made a fast retreat while you distracted the hostile ship.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The Engi can do remarkable things with just a pile of scrap. The Engi hive at this beacon are selling equipment for just that.

column11: The refugee ship thanks you for your assistance. As a gesture of good will (and seeing how effectively you dispatched the enemy ship), they offer up what supplies they can spare.
The outpost hails you, Thank you! I don't know what we did to anger the Rebels, but they were ready to kill us. I'll show you our goods and patch up your hull.
column12: System: teleporter, cloaking, battery, Augment: ION ARMOR, HACKING STUN, FLEET DISTRACTION,

column11: This was the site of a recent battle. Either a show of Mantis force, or the Engi here weren't disposed to go peacefully. You pick through the pieces.
You will have to be very cautious in this sector. The Rebels have full control and are no doubt looking for you.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The station was either abandoned or stripped clean. It seems to have lain unused for quite some time. You find nothing useful.
You feel naked without functioning sensors. You half expect a Rebel ship to appear from behind a cloud at any moment, but none come.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You arrive at a small space station that is putting out wide-band broadcasts on black-market channels. You doubt they would turn away any business, regardless of allegiances.

column11: There is a small planet nearby with scattered settlements. A small Rebel fleet is in orbit with many ships ferrying back and forth. It must be a more recently 'liberated' planet.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

You arrive to find yourself extremely close to a star. You receive a message from a pirate ship, I'm glad you arrived; our ship is damaged and we were getting desperate... I hope you don't mind if we take yours. Hostiles detected on board our ship!
You receive generic advertisements from a nearby public ship-yard. It seems they are willing to work on any ship, not only those of Rebel hue.

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
We understand... Please send help our way if you meet anyone trustworthy.
The Zoltan patrol their borders but let you pass when you ID as Federation. Let's hope they won't be so courteous to the Rebels.
The Zoltan stationed near this beacon are happy to receive you. As they give you the formal tour of their ship you spy some local star charts and mentally log the details.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

They finish: Please, spread the word of enlightenment to those that have not heard. Once you have, contact our brethren. They transmit coordinates of their so-called brethren. Added a quest marker to your map!

column11: Thank you for rescuing us! They held us hostage to ambush unsuspecting passersby. Please, take this.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The station was apparently designed to outfit Rebel ships with Drone Systems. You find a functioning Schematic.

Although your methods are crude and most certainly ineffective, it is clear you took our previous meeting to heart. If your ship represents the Federation's willingness to adapt we shall do what we can to aid in their fight. This technology should aid your quest.
Your crew are constantly looking out of the windows, checking for hostiles. They jump at every creak and moan of the ship. The tension is almost palpable...
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
A Mantis crew here has hunkered down in the abdomen of a long-dead space-whale - the only way, presumably, for them to operate their black-market trade without detection. Worth a look?
